			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Replication</span></h1>
			<div id="bodyContent">
				<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-revision-info">Revision as of 19:55, 17 December 2014 by <a href="/User:Rama" title="User:Rama" class="mw-userlink">Rama</a>  <span class="mw-usertoollinks">(<a href="/User_talk:Rama" title="User talk:Rama">Talk</a> | <a href="/Special:Contributions/Rama" title="Special:Contributions/Rama">contribs</a>)</span></div><br />
				<div id="mw-revision-nav">(<a href="/index.php?title=Replication&amp;diff=prev&amp;oldid=10734" title="Replication">diff</a>) <a href="/index.php?title=Replication&amp;direction=prev&amp;oldid=10734" title="Replication">← Older revision</a> | Latest revision (diff) | Newer revision → (diff)</div></div>
																<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>Networking is one of the many areas where Unreal Engine 4 shines. For those of you who have switched from Unity to Unreal Engine 4, or for those of you who are considering it: you are in for a pleasant surprise. UE4's network replication system is a master class in how to be awesome.
</p><p>This article will explain the details of object replication and make you a UE4 networking pro!
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><div id="toctitle"><h2>Contents</h2></div>
